{"word":"δηρός","slug":"δηρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δηρός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δήν'><el>δήν</el></a>\n<p/><i>long, too long</i>, <el>δηρὸν χρόνον</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; so, <el>δηρὸν</el> (<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>χρόνον</el>) as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>all too long</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>ἐπὶ δηρόν</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>δαρὸν χρόνον</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}